Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, then halve lengthways and scoop out the seeds (peel first if you prefer). Cut it widthways into 2cm slices, then again into 2cm cubes.

Pop the squash onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1}(drained) in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @water for the lentils{50%ml}, then stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @harissa paste{50%g}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the water has reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the sauce has reduced, stir in the lentils and cook for a further ~{2-3%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then remove from the heat.

Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

While the lentils cook, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily. When toasted, transfer them to a #bowl{} and set the pan aside.

Pop the @king prawns{150%g} into a #medium bowl{} with the @chermoula spice mix{1}. Season with @salt{}, then toss to coat the prawns well.

When everything is almost ready, pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

When the oil is hot, add the prawns and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

When everything is ready, stir the roasted butternut through the harissa lentils and spoon into your #bowls{} (reheat first if needed). Top with the chermoula prawns and drizzle over the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Finish with a sprinkling of toasted almonds over the top.

Enjoy!